 MBOMBELA – A fire broke out after 18:00 today at Crown National in Riverside Industrial Park.  According to one of the staff members, the fire broke out after all the staff had left.  Smoke billowing from the fire could be seen across the city.  “The alarm was activated that is why we know nobody was in the building at the time.”   ALSO READ; Poaching accused visit Kruger National Park freely Fire fighters and various emergency and security members are currently at the scene trying to fight the fire. Lowvelder will update as new information becomes available. ALSO READ: Woman raped after stopping to help someone  